revision.text:
'''Abu Bakr Ibn Al-Qutia''' (died 997) was a historian and author born in [[Córdoba, Spain]]. His mother was a [[Goths|Goth]] of royal lineage. His important historical account of [[Spain]] up to the [[Caliph of Cordoba]] [[Abd-ar-Rahman III]] (912–961) has been edited by [[Pascual de Gayangos]], and published with the translation of [[Julian Ribera y Tarrago|Julián Ribera y Tarragó]] as ''Historia de la conquista de España'' (1926).<ref>Allbio.co.uk</ref>

