{{Infobox royalty | name = Abubakar Garbai or Bukar Garbai | image = Shehu Abubakar Garbai of Borno.jpg | succession = | reign = 1902–1922 | predecessor = [[Sanda Wuduroma of Borno]] | successor = [[Sanda Kura of Borno]] | spouses = | issue = | dynasty = [[Kanemi]] | father = [[Ibrahim Kura]] | mother = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = 1922 | death_place = [[Borno State|Borno]] | place of burial = [[Kukawa]] | signature = | religion = [[Muslim]] |}}
'''Bukar Garbai''' (or '''Abubakar Garbai''') ibn Ibrahim was the Shehu of [[Borno State|Borno]] from 1902 to 1922.
==Reign== [[File:Shehu Abubakar Garbai of Borno in 1906.jpg|left|thumb|upright|Shehu Abubakar Garbai of Borno by [[Boyd Alexander]] in 1906]]
'''Bukar Garbai''' (or '''Abubakar Garbai''') ibn Ibrahim was the [[Borno Emirate|Shehu]] of [[Borno State|Bornu]] from 1902–1922 and previous to that served as Shehu of [[Dikwa emirate|Dikwa]]. In 1907 he founded [[Yerwa]] as the headquarters of his domains in connection with the British founding a military post in the same general location.
