'''Denis Caulfield Brady''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|JP|DL}} (1804 – 30 November 1886) was a [[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal]] Member of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]] who represented the [[United Kingdom constituencies|constituency]] of [[Newry (UK Parliament constituency)|Newry]]. He was a native of [[Newry]], the son of Thomas Brady and Rose Caulfield, and educated at [[Trinity College Dublin]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Walford |first1=Edward |title=The County Families of the United Kingdom|date=1869 |publisher=R. Hardwicke |page=120 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=C9EkzFlBgz0C&pg=PA120&dq=Denis+Caulfield+Brady |accessdate=20 June 2018 |language=en}}</ref> He was a reformer, in favour of the [[emancipation of Catholics]] and the [[Tithe War|abolition of tithes]], and he was elected through the support of the poor Catholics of Newry. As a result of Brady's victory over [[Staples baronets|Sir Thomas Staples]] in 1835, the [[Francis Jack Needham, 2nd Earl of Kilmorey|Earl of Kilmorey]] evicted more than 80 families from his lands for their votes.<ref>{{cite news |title=Earl Kilmorey's Tenantry |url=https://www.britishnewspaperarchive.co.uk/viewer/bl/0000829/18350314/001/0001 |accessdate=21 June 2018 |work=Newry Examiner |date=14 March 1835}}</ref> Brady became Chairman of the Newry Navigation Company and was also a Magistrate and [[Lord Lieutenant]] for [[County Down]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Stenton |first1=Michael |title=Who's who of British members of Parliament|date=1976 |publisher=The Harvester Press |isbn=9780855272197 |page=44 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DWQOAQAAMAAJ |accessdate=21 June 2018 |language=en}}</ref> He remained a devoted member of the Liberal Party, but toward the end of his life he increasingly supported the [[Unionism in Ireland|Unionist]] cause. He died in Newry, aged 82.<ref> ''Ireland, Civil Registration Deaths Index, 1864-1958''</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Death of Denis Caulfield Brady |url=https://www.britishnewspaperarchive.co.uk/viewer/bl/0000056/18861201/011/0003 |accessdate=20 June 2018 |work=Freeman's Journal |date=1 December 1886 |page=3}}</ref>

