'''Dennis Laurente''' (born July 29, 1977 in [[Palompon, Leyte|Palompon]], [[Leyte]], [[Philippines]]) is a [[Filipino people|Filipino]] professional [[Boxing|boxer]]. 

During his younger days, his family migrated to Agusan del Sur. He continued his studies in [[Sibagat]], [[Agusan del Sur]] and later in 1997, they migrated again in [[Agusan del Norte]] where he had a stint of work in a factory line making durian candy in [[Butuan City]]. Later, Laurente joined his parents in [[Leyte]] and did some work in the farm until he went to Manila to live with his uncle. A friend and pro boxer Aljun Corporal brought Laurente to Elorde in 1998.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dennis Laurente:Unlikely champ defies odds|url=https://www.philstar.com/sports/2001/12/26/144919/unlikely-champ-defies-odds#YjWPbaJW6Z4xoyfP.99}}</ref>

He fights under the care of Johnny S. Elorde, President of the Johnny Elorde Management International, and his wife, Liza Elorde, a boxing care manager.<ref>{{cite web
  | last = 
  | first = 
