'''Gene M. Gomes''' (January 22, 1946 &ndash; March 6, 2018) was an American judge.
Gomes was born in [[Fresno, California]]. He graduated from [[Fresno High School]] in 1963. Gomes received his bachelor's degree from [[Fresno State University]] in 1969 and then he received his law degree from [[McGeorge School of Law]] in 1972. He served as a deputy district attorney for [[Fresno County, California]]. Gomes practiced law in Fresno, California. In 1980, Gomes was appointed to the Fresno Municipal Court. Then, in 1982, he was appointed to the Fresno Superior Court. Gomes served on the [[California Courts of Appeal]] from 2002 until his death. Gomes died in Fresno, California.<ref>[http://www.courts.ca.gov/4017.htm California Courts of Appeal-Gene M. Gomes]</ref><ref>[http://gvwire.com/2018/03/longtime-fresno-judge-dies/ Longtime Fresno Judge dies. Gomes was 'Witty, Fun & Brilliant.']</ref>
