'''Higinia Bartolomé de Alamo''' was a Venezuelan poet and writer from [[Barquisimeto]]. A contemporary of professor [[Alberto Castillo Arráez]],<ref name=Acosta2012>{{cite news|last1=Acosta|first1=Otto|title=Ateneos|language=Spanish|url=http://elimpulso.com/articulo/ateneos|accessdate=10 January 2015|publisher=''El Impulso''|date=14 August 2012}}</ref> she was the wife of Dr. Antonio Alamo (1873-1953),<ref name="Rodríguez1957">{{cite book|last=Rodríguez|first=Ramón Armando|title=Diccionario biográfico, geográfico e histórico de Venezuela|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7EsuAAAAIAAJ|year=1957|location=Madrid, Spain|language=Spanish|pages=13}}</ref> Minister of Development and governor of [[Bolívar (state)|Bolívar state]] during the government of [[Juan Vicente Gómez]].

