{{one source|date=September 2017}}
'''Hyman Abrams''' was a [[Boston]] mobster and high-ranking member under [[Charles Solomon (racketeer)|Charles "King" Solomon]] during Prohibition. He and other members of Solomon's organization took over Boston's criminal operations for themselves following Solomon's murder in 1933. He would later become involved in financing syndicate controlled casinos with [[Meyer Lansky]], specifically the ''[[Flamingo Las Vegas|Flamingo]]'' and later the ''[[Sands Casino|Sands]]'' with [[Carl Cohen (businessman)|Carl Cohen]] and [[Jack Entratter]].

