{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}} {{Use British English|date=July 2014}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Jack Bryan | image = | caption = | fullname = John Joseph Bryan<ref name=LCFCarchive/> | birth_date = {{birth date|1897|8|22|df=y}}<ref name=LCFCarchive/> | birth_place = [[Langwith, Derbyshire|Langwith]], England | death_date = {{death year and age|1978|1897}}<ref name=LCFCarchive/> | death_place = | height = | position = [[Right half]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = – | clubs1 = Langwith Red Rose | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = – | clubs2 = Mansfield Swifts | caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = – | clubs3 = [[Shirebrook Miners Welfare F.C.|Shirebrook]] | caps3 = | goals3 = | years4 = 1918–1922 | clubs4 = [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]]<ref group=lower-alpha>Figures are for appearances and goals in [[the Football League]] only. The free-access sections of the Lincoln City FC Archive does not separate appearances by competition other than for the Football League.</ref>| caps4 = 75 | goals4 = 1 | years5 = – | clubs5 = [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]] | caps5 = | goals5 = | years6 = – | clubs6 = [[Worksop Town F.C.|Worksop Town]] | caps6 = | goals6 = | years7 = – | clubs7 = [[Mexborough Athletic F.C.|Mexborough]] | caps7 = | goals7 = }}
'''John Joseph '''"'''Jack'''"''' Bryan''' (22 August 1897 – 1978) was an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who made 75 appearances in [[the Football League]] for [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]]. He played as a [[right half]].<ref name=Joyce/>
==Life and career== Bryan was born in [[Langwith, Derbyshire|Langwith]], [[Nottinghamshire]].<ref name=LCFCarchive/> He played local football in the Nottinghamshire area<ref name=Joyce/> before joining [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]] towards the end of the First World War. He played in all but three senior matches in the first post-war season, as Lincoln finished 21st in the [[Football League Second Division|Second Division]] and failed to gain [[re-election (Football League)|re-election]], and missed only two as they won the [[Midland Football League#Midland League 1889–1960|Midland League]] title and returned to the Football League as founder members of the [[Football League Third Division North|Third Division North]]. He again played all but two matches in the [[1921–22 Football League|1921–22 season]],<ref name=LCFCarchive/> one of which was [[goalkeeper (association football)|in goal]] after [[Bob Bainbridge|Robert Bainbridge]] missed his train to the away game at [[Durham City A.F.C.|Durham City]].<ref name=goal/> At the end of the season he moved into the Midland League with [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]], and later played for [[Worksop Town F.C.|Worksop Town]] and [[Mexborough Athletic F.C.|Mexborough]].<ref name=Joyce/>
